video:video.video:description: Follow The Associated Press’ Isabel DeBre as she takes you inside Argentina’s Patagonia region, which is seeing some of the worst wildfires to hit the region in decades.

video:video.video:title: Punxsutawney Phil is said to have seen his shadow, predicting 6 more weeks of winter weather
video:video.video:description: Punxsutawney Phil is said to be predicting six more weeks of wintry weather after he saw his shadow Monday.

video:video.video:title: Linkin Park founder on 'starting from scratch'
video:video.video:description: Speaking at the Grammy Awards, Linkin Park's Mike Shinoda discusses how the band moved forward after the untimely death of their lead singer, Chester Bennington, stating they were "literally starting from scratch."

video:video.video:title: Trucks full of aid supplies go through Rafah Gate to be inspected at Kerem Shalom crossing
video:video.video:description: Trucks full of aid supplies and blankets entered Egypt's Rafah Gate on Sunday, heading to Kerem Shalom crossing for Israeli inspection. (AP video by Mohammad Arafat)

video:video.video:title: Iran’s supreme leader warns any US attack would spark ‘regional war’
video:video.video:description: Iran’s supreme leader warned Sunday that any attack by the United States would spark a “regional war” in the Mideast, further escalating tensions as President Donald Trump has threatened to militarily strike the Islamic Republic, over its crackdown on recent nationwide protests.

video:video.video:title: Ethiopian rebel leader rejects accusations of targeting civilians in rare interview from hideout
video:video.video:description: Oromia is Ethiopia’s country’s biggest state, with 35% of the population and the Federal Republic’s capital, Addis Ababa.

video:video.video:title: Cuban diplomat tells the AP there's no dialogue with the US but the island is open to one
video:video.video:description: A senior Cuban diplomat told The Associated Press on Monday that his government does not have a “table of dialogue” with the United States but is open to one if certain criteria are met as tensions remain high between the two countries.

video:video.video:title: Bad Bunny arrives at the Grammys
video:video.video:description: Bad Bunny arrives at the Grammys. His critically acclaimed album “Debí Tirar Más Fotos” is only the second Spanish-language record to be nominated for album of the year, with the first being his 2022 album “Un Verano Sin Ti.”

video:video.video:title: Tyla walks the Grammys red carpet
video:video.video:description: Tyla walks the red carpet at the 68th annual Grammy Awards.

video:video.video:title: Mexico’s push for US natural gas sparks community opposition and threatens its climate pledges
video:video.video:description: Fishermen, Indigenous communities and environmental groups along Mexico's southern coast are raising alarms over a massive underwater natural gas pipeline they say threatens fragile coral reefs and families' livelihoods.

video:video.video:title: Bangladesh’s ex-leader Hasina and her UK lawmaker niece sentenced in graft case
video:video.video:description: A court in Bangladesh on Monday sentenced former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina to 10 years in jail and her niece Tulip Siddiq, who is a British lawmaker, to four years in prison in two cases involving a government township project near the capital.

video:video.video:title: Kehlani Arrives at Grammys Red Carpet
video:video.video:description: Kehlani arrives at the 68th annual Grammys Awards wearing an “ICE OUT” pin.
